[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mg qianzhidezi 01||The pin is the subject of discussion in this board.||When trying to apply the pin, you try to use one piece to pin your opponent's two pieces at one time with one of your piece. If used correctly, it may result in a gain in material.||||====||||Tactic: ||Capturing Material By Trapping ||???? 01||||???? Capturing your opponent's pieces by trapping them is the tactic discussed in this page. ||This another one of the most basic tactics to learn.||Sometimes, a poorly positioned or rootless piece might be captured. Instead of directly attacking it, you trap it like a hunter. You corner it with a few moves, rendering it helpless before the final capturet.||Please note that this tactic is only deemed successful when throughout the process of capturing, you do not lose any positional advantage or control of the game; otherwise it is not worth the trouble![/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
